cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with visual perception tasks related to automated driving, specifically object detection and semantic segmentation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions the use of a low power embedded SOC, which suggests a focus on robotics and automation, leading to the possibility of cs.RO (Robotics) as a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of neural networks and optimization, indicating a possible fit with cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper mentions the use of a ResNet10 like encoder, which is a type of neural network architecture, suggesting a possible fit with cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
